wikipedia_page.main: James William Chappell (3 March 1915 – 3 April 1973), also known as Jim Chappell and Jimmy Chappell, was an ice hockey player who played in the English National League (ENL). He is known for playing for the Great Britain national ice hockey team which won the gold medal at the 1936 Winter Olympics. He is a member of the British Ice Hockey Hall of Fame.
